net.marfgamer.jraknet.protocol

Enum ConnectionType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ConnectionType>
      • net.marfgamer.jraknet.protocol.ConnectionType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ConnectionType>

    public enum ConnectionType
extends java.lang.Enum<ConnectionType>
    Used to signify which implementation of the RakNet protocol is being used by a connection. If you would like your implementation to be listed here, create an issue on the JRakNet repository with the tag "Connection type support". Keep in mind that this functionality has no guarantees to function completely, as it is completely dependent on the implementation to implement this feature.
    Author:
    Whirvis "MarfGamer" Ardenaur
    See Also:
    https://github.com/JRakNet/JRakNet/issues/new
